###
### Enterprise Travel & Expense Management System - API Test Suite
###
### This file contains all API requests for testing the entire project.
### Use the REST Client extension in VS Code to run these requests.
###
### Requirements:
### - API running on http://localhost:5142
### - REST Client extension installed
###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5142/api
@contentType = application/json

###
### ============================================================================
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================================================
###

### Login as Employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "employee@example.com",
  "role": "Employee"
}

### Login as Manager
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "manager@example.com",
  "role": "Manager"
}

### Login with invalid role (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "role": "Admin"
}

### Login with missing email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "role": "Employee"
}

###
### ============================================================================
### TRAVEL REQUESTS ENDPOINTS
### ============================================================================
###

### Create Travel Request - Valid
### Note: Replace {{token}} with actual token from login response
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Paris",
  "startDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-05-20T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Different destination
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "London",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-06-05T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Long duration trip
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Tokyo",
  "startDate": "2026-07-10T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-07-25T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Invalid: Empty destination (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "",
  "startDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-05-20T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Invalid: Past start date (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Berlin",
  "startDate": "2025-01-01T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2025-01-05T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Invalid: End date before start date (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Madrid",
  "startDate": "2026-05-20T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Create Travel Request - Invalid: Invalid user ID (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Rome",
  "startDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-05-20T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 999
}

### Create Travel Request - Missing authorization (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Amsterdam",
  "startDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-05-20T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

###
### Get All Travel Requests - No filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by status: Pending
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by status: Approved
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Approved
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by status: Rejected
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Rejected
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by status: Completed
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Completed
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by status: Cancelled
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Cancelled
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Filter by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?startDateFrom=2026-05-01T00:00:00Z&endDateTo=2026-06-01T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Multiple filters: status and date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Pending&startDateFrom=2026-05-01T00:00:00Z&endDateTo=2026-08-01T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Travel Requests - Without authorization (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests

###
### Get Travel Request by ID - Valid (replace {id} with actual ID from creation response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Travel Request by ID - Non-existent (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/9999
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Travel Request by ID - Without authorization (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1

###
### Approve Travel Request - Valid (requires Manager role)
### Note: Replace {{managerToken}} with token from manager login
### Note: Replace {id} with actual travel request ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{managerToken}}

### Approve Travel Request - As Employee (should fail - requires Manager role)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### Approve Travel Request - Non-existent request (should fail)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/9999/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{managerToken}}

### Approve Travel Request - Without authorization (should fail)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1/approve

###
### ============================================================================
### EXPENSES ENDPOINTS
### ============================================================================
###

### Submit Expense - Valid (for approved travel request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 150.50,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Hotel accommodation in Paris"
}

### Submit Expense - Multiple items for same trip
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 75.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Meals and dining"
}

### Submit Expense - With receipt file (base64-encoded example)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 200.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "description": "Transportation - Flight ticket",
  "receiptBase64": "JVBERi0xLjQKJeLjz9MNCjEgMCBvYmo=",
  "receiptFileName": "flight_receipt.pdf"
}

### Submit Expense - Different currency
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 180.00,
  "currency": "GBP",
  "description": "Restaurant - Dinner"
}

### Submit Expense - Large amount
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 5000.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Conference registration fee"
}

### Submit Expense - Invalid: Missing required fields (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1
}

### Submit Expense - Invalid: Negative amount (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": -50.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Invalid expense"
}

### Submit Expense - Invalid: Zero amount (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 0,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Invalid expense"
}

### Submit Expense - Invalid: Non-existent travel request (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 9999,
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Expense for non-existent trip"
}

### Submit Expense - Invalid: Travel request not approved (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 2,
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Expense for pending trip"
}

###
### ============================================================================
### COMPLETE WORKFLOW SCENARIO
### ============================================================================
###
### Step 1: Employee logs in
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john.doe@company.com",
  "role": "Employee"
}

### Step 2: Employee creates a travel request
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "New York",
  "startDate": "2026-08-15T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-08-22T00:00:00Z",
  "userId": 1
}

### Step 3: Get all pending travel requests
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Step 4: Manager logs in
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "jane.smith@company.com",
  "role": "Manager"
}

### Step 5: Manager retrieves specific request (replace {id} with ID from step 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1
Authorization: Bearer {{managerToken}}

### Step 6: Manager approves the travel request (replace {id} with ID from step 2)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{managerToken}}

### Step 7: Employee submits expenses for approved trip (employee logs in again)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john.doe@company.com",
  "role": "Employee"
}

### Step 8: Submit first expense
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 250.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Hotel - 7 nights in Manhattan"
}

### Step 9: Submit second expense
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": 1,
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Meals and transportation"
}

### Step 10: View all travel requests to see approved status
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests?status=Approved
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
### ============================================================================
### ERROR HANDLING TEST CASES
### ============================================================================
###

### Test: Invalid JWT token
GET {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_12345

### Test: Malformed JSON in request body
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Paris"
  "startDate": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z"
}

### Test: Empty request body
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### Test: Invalid date format
POST {{baseUrl}}/travelrequests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "destination": "Paris",
  "startDate": "invalid-date",
  "endDate": "2026-05-20",
  "userId": 1
}

### Test: String value for numeric field
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "travelRequestId": "invalid",
  "amount": 100,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Test"
}
